At the same time, they acknowledge that the picture is not all sunny — the virus in some countries is likely spreading unchecked.
The pandemic is exposing major flaws in higher-income countries’ health systems and turning the tables on decades of travel restrictions targeting Africans.
Four years later, Africa is at risk of contamination primarily from Europe, China, and the U.S.
The Democratic Republic of Congo imposed quarantine measures on travelers from Italy, France, China, and Germany.
The U.S. decided not to use WHO’s kits, according to Dr. Ashish Jha, a director of Harvard University’s Global Health Institute.